    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the contrast injection painful?",
        "answer": " Most feel only a warm flush; mild nausea is rare.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " How long does the full test take?",
        "answer": " 30 minutes from check-in to discharge.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home after the scan?",
        "answer": " Yes, unless sedated for claustrophobia.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if my creatinine is high?",
        "answer": " We’ll hydrate you and consider non-contrast MRI or nephrologist review.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " What happens after the scan?",
        "answer": "You can typically leave immediately after the procedure and resume your normal diet and daily activities. We strongly recommend that you drink plenty of water for the rest of the day to help your kidneys flush the contrast dye from your system."
      }
